<Review>Needed my CPR Re-Certification quickly! There were a variety of scheduled classes to choose from, even weekends.  With Covid, you cannot do a full in person course. The virtual class, via Canvas, supplied by AHA was very good. The course was easy to follow, with lots of examples (SIMS and human). The exam was straight forward and hit on all the key points to doing CPR.  The hands on CPR was limited but since it was re-cert, it was enough of a review. The staff was helpful and took Covid safety and cleanliness seriously.   I got my CPR card and certificate emailed in 24 hours. It was a great experience and I will use them again.</Review>< pics>

<Date>1618828840670<//Date><pics>None< /pics>< Text>
Getting my AHA BLS certification at Critical Care Education in Fontana was a simple and fast process. The course is split into two parts, an online portion and an in-person skills portion. During registration, the date and time that you choose for the course is actually when you'll be required to show up and demonstrate your skills in person, so keep that in mind when registering.

Jonathan, my instructor, was very informative and helpful. He was patient with me and thorough in his explanations during the skills part of my course. I will definitely be renewing my BLS with Critical Care in the future.</Text>

< Text>
Took my 2 year old here for her first dentist appointment, the staff were incredibly patient and kind. From the moment we entered to checking out, everyone was friendly and accommodating to my toddler. The staff had concerns about her teeth but would not do the cavity screening for fear of scaring her. This resulted in me having to take her to a pediatric dentist, I wish they had just done the screening because it simply involved poking her teeth with the instrument. This visit was good overall.

Returned for a cleaning for myself, and had a completely different experience. The dentist was wonderful, I enjoyed my visit with her and she was thorough. The hygienist on the other hand was a terrible experience. She was very rough, scraping underneath my gums, causing a lot of bleeding, and ignoring my obvious pain. I was unable to floss for several days without pain after this appointment. I did not have any tooth concerns, cavities, and am diligent with my dental hygiene, this cleaning was unnecessarily painful, I had never had an experience like it. I wish I had the wherewithal to stop the cleaning and express my confusion, but I didn't. I had hoped the amount of blood and constant wincing was plenty, but I should have said something. I recommend the dentist, but encourage others to have caution with your hygienist and speak up if it is painful.<//Text>

< review>
I have a 2007 FXSTC, We all have our reasons  but my bike means a lot to me. It's got a stage one kit, specifically Rush pipes (1.75) HD high flow air and a FP3.
I started with a decel pop, spoke with the folks at Vance & Hines (VH) and they helped me figure out where I screwed up. so, fixed. Couple years go by and I start to have a really bizarre idle problem, I'm chasing a ghost here, all the blogs read exactly as my experience is but no one has an answer. (long winded sorry)
I reach out to VH and get help from C.M. (I hope VH knows who this is as he deserves recognition)..now..my FP3 is out of warranty but the help I get never questions that, this guy just wants to help, he tells me things about the FP3 I wasn't aware of. I'm uploading my maps, he's making adjustments, I'm downloading and remapping, I'm sending feedback and this guy is getting back to me quickly and making more adjustments, this goes on for awhile with some success but ultimately I ended up taking it to the dealership,  This is where it gets really good, The dealership says a lot of times its a tuner problem but once they see the exchanges between me and this guy at VH? the maps, the adjustments, tuner is ruled out immediately and they are like whoa?  No excuses allowed here, we need to figure this out and its not the tuner.
Its because of the help I received that the tuner was not an easy excuse
Its because of the help I received that the dealership had a direction to go when diagnosing the issue
Its because of the help I received that I'm writing this long winded Thank You to C.M. and the folks at VH for standing behind their product and helping their customers. Now I feel bad for not buying VH after market pipes! (i like my rush pipes though) I also like the service department at my dealership, the mechanic is great, their service advisor is great so I have no complaint there, but the VH customer service is a rare find today, I appreciate it, I will champion it for VH and I will recommend VH to anyone. I appreciate the help and say thanks...That's my experience</review>

<name>Scott Register< /name></record></dataset><record>
<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Food:
* The meats and cheeses are all Boar's Head, so it's good quality.
* Good variety of items on their menu (wraps, sandwiches, burgers, much more), and the prices are good.
* They run daily specials and have an email listing you can sign up for.
* Beverages: several coolers of sodas, energy drinks, teas, sports drinks, etc. There's fountain drinks too.

Service:
* Always great and out quick.
* I go here a lot and have never had any complaints.
* Delivery available for places nearby.

Misc / Notes:
* Indoor & outdoor seating.
* Good atmosphere, it has that mom & pop feel.
* Great lunch spot for employees on the industrial parkway, and worth the drive from Poway Road if you're coming from that direction.
* It's easy to pass up. Right across the street from Sysco and next door to the Body For Life.</Review>

< Review>
I went to this location on Tuesday with my boyfriend to try out the food since it seemed like a really good place to eat Mexican food at. We were completely wrong. We ordered online, there was a 35 minute wait for our food, which we did not mind. When the 35 minutes came by, I went into the store. I was not greeted by anyone so I went up to the girl who seems to be helping people with online orders. I told her that I was there to pick up food and gave her my name. She just kept looking at me and then stared at my phone. I asked her if she needed the email for confirmation and with attitude she said yes. She then wrote down my name and told me to wait outside. I waiting for 10 minutes after the 35 minutes I was required to wait. I went inside and since she was not around, I waited for her to come back. Before talking to her, the client she was talking to said he had been waiting for an hour already. I asked her "how much longer until I receive my order" and she just stared at me and nodded and walked away. Meanwhile she went to help another client to look for his order, he mentioned that he was waiting for an hour and 30 minutes which seems ridiculous for the fact that it was a pick up order and people in the drive thru and walking into the store were getting their orders faster. When I got my order, the quesadilla I ordered was no even cooked throughly. The cheese was not melted at all and was still chunky, also full of grease. I also ordered the tacitos and the plate was a mess. It did not even seem like an effort was made to put it together. We also ordered a surf and turf bowl which was missing the carne asada. The ceviche was leaking which made the tostadas soggy. This was one of my worse customer experiences at your location and they should properly  train their employees because our money is paying their bills.<//Review>

I rarely write reviews but this experience took the cake. I phoned in. The person taking orders was rude but I figured they were probably stressed. I made this call around 12:35. I was told to park and walk-in and it would be around 20-25 minutes. I was in no rush so I went in at 1. I paid at the front and was told to wait outside. I want to preface this next part with im pretty patient, probably to a fault. The people who walked in and ordered all got their food before me. All of the phone orders are taken to one of the front tables and you can see when they bring them out. I was a little frustrated at this point as I waited 45 minutes only for walk-in orders to be ahead of me. I went back inside to look at the finished orders as I had seen others do before. The cashier was extremely rude and told me to get out. I saw my name but I still exited as I didn't want to cause even more of a commotion. I waited another 15 minutes for the runner to come back to the front. She finally came out and I asked her about my order and she said oh its been here, she grabbed it for me and I left. It was about an hour and five minutes from phone order to getting my food. I hate to write this review because otherwise their food is amazing. My order was not ready. They asked me to wait outside (covid, I get it). Twenty minutes goes by and my food STILL isn't ready (I only get a 30 minute lunch break).
They don't apologize, nor offer anything to make it right. They just refund my money.
Then I look at the receipt they gave me, they charged me for someone else's order! I'd been waiting for food that wasn't even mine!

<rating>5< /rating>< review>
I came here on Tuesday at lunch and it was a bit of a line. Took about 15 min to get my items. The place has small but had a cool red and yellow theme going. The design and layout were modern and inviting. They have promotion from Monday thru Thursday every week! Tuesday is $1 fish tacos and Weds is $2 shrimp tacos. I ordered 2 fish tacos. They were piping hot and tasted awesome! The fish were cripsy with delicious topping sauce. The side stand had red onion, lime, and orange bell pepper. The tables had a good selection of hot sauce so you can keep every bite spicy! Will have to come back to try out more from the menu!<//review>

<Review>I've tried the aguachiles tostada, fish tacos, carne asada tacos, chicken tacos, potatoe tacos, shrimp cocktail, asada sope, chicken sope, horchata, and cucumber water. I love the fish tacos the best. Their meat isn't lean, so if you don't like eating fat, you'll have to pick it out of your food like I do. If you like spicy foods try the aguachiles and get that cucumber water with mint and chia seeds. It's the most refreshing drink! A good meatless option are the potatoe tacos, they're delicious.
If you go on a Tuesday, the line goes all the way outside and it was way too crowded to eat inside because the fish tacos are 99cents each. On Thursdays the meat tacos are 99cents each.

*UPDATE* Feb 2018
I recently also tried the barbacoa tacos, pi√±a agua fresca and strawberry agua fresca. All three were really good.  I gave it another go with the carne asada and chicken and ordered sopes but their meat still isn't clean so I couldn't eat 80% of it. I even ASK before ordering if their meat has "cuero". The cashier thought I meant skin and had me ask one of the cooks and he said it was clean (but it wasn't like always) -.- so I'll stick to the fish tacos and barbacoa!

<review>Very tasty, reasonably cheap fish tacos.Nicely fried, flavorful, with tasty sides and sauce.  It seems like they have dollar fish tacos on Tuesday which I will for sure be coming back for.
I found that other items on the menu were closer to average. The pastor and carne asada tacos I had were both relatively tasty, but the meat itself didn't seem to be of great quality. The "crab" ceviche is actually made of imitation crab(I should have known from the cheap price). The strawberry agua fresca is delicious and not too sweet. Their condiment and sides bar is extensive, with radishes, onions, and large banana peppers available.

The service is just okay, and we had to wait a decent amount of time for our food.

Overall I would definitely come back and probably just order the fish tacos.</review>< pictures>
None</pictures>
